Package rest

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AuthenticationDemoService
    Minimal HTTP authentication demo, authenticating user "sascha" with password "sascha": /services/authentication/basic: HTTP "Basic authorization" /services/authentication/digest: HTTP "Digest authorization" Once a user is authenticated, changing the authentication method or the user-alias, or the password, requires a browser cache clearance or restart.

    Some notes regarding Basic and Digest authentication: With realm set to "", the transferred response for Digest authentication is MD5(MD5(alias::password)::MD5(httpMethod:uri)).
    EntityService
    JAX-RS based REST service implementation for polymorphic entity resources.
    LifeCycleProviderSkeleton
    This life-cycle provider is a singleton adapter and deploys the following services for REST services: Entity manager life-cycle management: Entity managers are created upon the begin of any HTTP request, and closed at the end of it.
